am Bhagwan. Would you agree to this conclusion? :) &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_387&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apparently in the Brahma Vaivarta Purana, Suta tells the Rishis of Naimisharanya that Krshna is greatest Avatara of them all.&lt;/span&gt; So, how do we resolve this apparent conflict between what Rishi Parashara states and what this Purana states? If it is a matter of personal choice, then of course matter ends here.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;&lt;If one does\n not try to\n understand the nature, essence and\n purpose of \neach avatara and looks at superficial things like the physical body they\n came in, and tries to fit them in some pattern, one will only draw \nsuperficial conclusions.&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Unless one can provide very convincing answers as to why these 9 are considered in the list of Dasavataras and NOT others like Mohini or Danwantari who are also mentioned as Avataras, I am afraid the world will keep getting more and more convinced that this specific list of dasavataras represent a parable of evoluion, where One Being comes in 9 different forms, in 9 different times, for 9 different purposes to guide the process of evolution of life and consciousness in the manifested world on planet earth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Regards&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_81 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_95&quot; style=&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:16px;font-family:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span\n class=&quot;yiv1276886991Apple-style-span&quot; style=&quot;font-size:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span