, as per Parasara. In contrast, the 5th and 6th\n avataras did have some jeevatmamsa in them.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;&lt;I mean Dattatreya is an Avatara too as per SB. His spirituality is no less than that of any other Avatara. Yet, he is not in the list of 9/10 Avataras.&gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;First of all, dasavataras are not a &quot;top 10&quot; short-list of SB&#39;s list. SB list gives the avataras of Supreme Being (&quot;Purusha&quot; as it calls). Dasavataras OTOH are specifically of Vishnu, who is the &quot;sustaining principle&quot; of Purusha. Dattatreya is an avatara of Brahma, Vishnu and Shiva together, i.e. creative, sustaining and destructive principles of Purusha combined together. That is why he is not among Dasavataras. That does not make him any less or more. His purpose/functionality is simply different from that of Rama, Krishna, Narasimha, or Venkateswara. Just in terms of\n &quot;popularity&quot;, he is actually more popular than\n some of the dasavataras.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Secondly, rather than *comparing* avataras in terms like &quot;less&quot; or more in &quot;spirituality&quot;, try to *understand* avataras from the point of view of what functionality and role they play in the functioning of collective cosmic consciousness. THAT is the key to understanding them and their place in cosmos. And also to internalizing them eventually..&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Whether you call the Supreme Being as Purusha or Krishna or Shiva or Surya or Narayana does not really matter, for Scriptures are clear that He is beyond names or descriptions.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;If your devotion to Him is steadfast, if your notion of Him expands with time beyond the initial notions you start off with, and if the paramatmamsa in you is able to resonate to Him and the conditioning of your jeevatmamsa is being overcome, that is all\n that\n matters!&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology &amp; Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br id=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_63&quot;&gt;&lt;blockquote id=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_66&quot; style=&quot;border-left:2px solid rgb(16, 16, 255);&quot;&gt;  &lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_70 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_123 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_137&quot; style=&quot;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_71 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_124 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_138&quot; style=&quot;font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot; size=&quot;2&quot;&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; rajarshi nandy &lt;rajarshi14@...&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;\n &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; &lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;\n Monday, May 6, 2013 8:07 AM&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Subject:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Comparing Dasavataras!&lt;br&gt; &lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991y_msg_container&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;yiv1276886991&quot;&gt;\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;\n\n\n\n    &lt;div id=&quot;yiv1276886991ygrp-text&quot;&gt;\n      \n      \n      &lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_80 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_130 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_144&quot; style=&quot;color:#000;background-color:#fff;font-family:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;font-size:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dear Narasimha,&lt;var id=&quot;yiv1276886991yui-ie-cursor&quot;&gt;&lt;/var&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_81 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_131 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_145&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_82 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_132 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_146&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jai Ma!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_83 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_133 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_147&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_84 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_134 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_148&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Some freeflowing thoughts that struck me while thinking about some of points you have raised. I am just doing a thinking aloud here. Feel free to disagree :)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_85 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_135 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_149&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_86 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_136 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_150&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Firstly, I feel, the conception of colloquially used&nbsp;term&nbsp;Bhagawan as a Superman with unlimited potentials way beyond what any normal human being can achieve, came into existence from the Vaishnava schools of Kali Yuga, who looked at Krshna as the ultimate God&nbsp;on earth. It is difficult to miss the phonetic&nbsp;similarity between terms Bhagawata and Bhagawana. The Bhagawata religion started from the Gita and a contemplation of the life of Krshna. All the major purely&nbsp;Vaishnava Acharyas - Ramanujacharya, Madhavacharya, Vallavacharya, Nimbarka, Sri Chaitanya&nbsp;as well as the nava-naths (Dhaneshwari was the earliest known non-sanskrit\n translation of\n the Gita) - considered, (with\n differing\n nuances on the&nbsp;relation between\n jiva,\n paramatma, moksha&nbsp;etc), Krshna as the ultimate conception of God on earth. This was aided in no less a measure by the delcaration of the earliest Puranas, that is Vishnu Purana and the SB, that Krshna was a complete Avatara. Some, like the Gaudiya Vaishnavas, went one step ahead and took a very literal view of it all and declared Krshna as the Ultimate Being, and the formless Paramatma, as well as Narayana,&nbsp;as merely&nbsp;the aura of Krshna. Rama was also intricately linked to this Krshnaa-ism, but was looked at as the earlier brith of Krshna, not as a separate Divity in himself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_87 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_137 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_151&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_88 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_138 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_152&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Whatever the case maybe, each school had its own set of established saints and scholars to vouch for their views. So it boiled down to interpretation, which is often, as you rightly pointed out, based on&nbsp;various conditionings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_89 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_139 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_153&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_90 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_140 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_154&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;We&nbsp;human beings are creatures of imagination. Whenever an Avatar appears on the earth,&nbsp;most of the great Mahatmas who appear after the Avatara, remain&nbsp;overawed by the&nbsp;character of the last Avatara&nbsp;because invariable in the context of the desh-kaal-patra of those times, the life of the Avatara shows actions performed which are&nbsp;way beyond&nbsp;imagination for *those times*. Such a situation continues until the next Avatara comes on earth. I am sure in the period after Rama, and before Krshna, of which we have very little written record, the world at large remained entirely overawed by Rama Avatara.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_91 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_141 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_155&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_92 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_142 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_156&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;In this light Krshna is the Poorna-Avatara. When Kalki will appear on earth, he will be invarible accompanied by a set of powerful Rishis - every Avatara comes with his &lt;font size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;yiv1276886991vk_ans yiv1276886991vk_bk&quot;&gt;coterie of Rishis who explain the philosophy and spirituality of the Avatara to the general masses - who will then create new scriptures and Kalki will be looked at as the crest jewel&nbsp;of the Avataras.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_93 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_143 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_157&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;*&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_94 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_144 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_158&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_95 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_145 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_159&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;I believe in the evolutionary parable of these 9 Avatara because I find no other reason why these set of Avatara, from the whole list of possible&nbsp;Avataras, have captured the popular imagination. I mean Dattatreya is an Avatara too as per SB. His spirituality is no less than that of any other Avatara. Yet, he is not in the list of 9/10 Avataras. &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_96 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_146 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_160&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_97 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_147 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_161&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;The&nbsp;original Nath Yogis used to consider&nbsp;Nine Chakras in the Human Body. The idea of Kundalini Yoga also came from them, which was basically exploring&nbsp;cronologically all these nine chakras one after the other by flooding them with Chit-Shakti.&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_98 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_148 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_162&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_99 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_149 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_163&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;There are 9 basic grahas in jyotish. Each graha could very well&nbsp;represent the essential nature of each chakra. All these make me more sanguine that there must be Nine Evolutionary Avataras, not ten. In which case Kalki must be the Ninth Avatara.&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_100 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_150 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_164&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_101 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_151 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_165&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;Buddha, as you rightly pointed out,&nbsp;has a tremendous logical appeal in Kali Yuga. But if logic is the criteria, then why not Adi Shankara? I may not agree to&nbsp;his philosophy as it comes down to us from his followers, but it cannot be denied that&nbsp;Adi Shankara was&nbsp;arguable one of the sharpest and most logical of spiritual philosphers. His intellectual and logical mind&nbsp;is beyond doubt.&nbsp;Just that Shankara&nbsp;never claimed himself to be an Avatara. Neither did&nbsp;Siddhartha. Only that the later came 3000 years ago, and the former came possibly in the last 1000 years.&nbsp;Shankara&#39;s spiritual impact on the world is no less than\n that of\n the&nbsp;Buddha. What\n mainstream&nbsp;Hinduism today is,\n could not have been, had it\n not been for\n the invaluable\n contribution of Adi Shankara. And if Buddha was truly&nbsp;the awaited&nbsp;9th Avatara of Vishnu, Shankara would not have been able to absorb the philosophy of Buddha into Hinduism and thus make it lose its grip on India. Buddhism barely exists in land of its birth.&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_102 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_152 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_166&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_103 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_153 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_167&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;All this taken together, make me more and more convinced that there are 9 evolutionary Avataras and the 9th is yet to come.&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_104 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_154 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_168&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_105 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_155 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_169&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;*&nbsp; *&nbsp; *&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_106 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_156 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_170&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_107 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_157 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_171&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;A little bit about Rama and Krshna. When I said I admire Rama, it is not a lip-service. There are incidents in the Ramayana which I find extremely inspiring, educative and uplifting. Like the incident where Rama was to cross the ocean. Rama knew very well that if he wanted, in one moment he could have used his Divine Astras and forced the ocean to yield way to his army. Yet he sat in silent supplication for days, praying that the ocean allow his army safe passage. When all else failed, when genuine goodwill was not recirpocated, and it was absolutely necessary to cross the ocean,&nbsp;THEN&nbsp;Rama took up weapons to get the job done.&nbsp;A powerful\n warrior,&nbsp;who\n knows&nbsp;very well how&nbsp;powerful\n he&nbsp;himself is, not letting that sense\n of power\n pervert his mind even\n for a moment is an amazing phenomenon. This kind of self-control is rare and worthy of comtemplation, specially by anyone who feels, ever so slightly, that he/she has some form of power or influence in this world in any sphere.&nbsp;Rama had no malice for anyone. Not even Ravana, by the end of the war at least. He was the very personification of Satwa. In Satwa, conflict and malice and cunningness are impossible.&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_108 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_158 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_172&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_109 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_159 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_173&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;Recently, a friend of mine told me that he has learnt all his life that one must listen to Krshna&#39;s advice, but only follow what Rama did, and not what Krshna did. I disagree with this vehemently. If one reads entire Krshna&#39;s life&nbsp;with an objective mind, Krshna of Vrndavana, Krshna of Mathura, Krshna of Kurushetra, Krshna the Jagat Guru who speaks the Gita, one will find that what Krshna the Guru adviced in the Gita,&nbsp;Krshna the&nbsp;Divine Worker&nbsp;himself followed it all through his life at every instance. It is his&nbsp;perfect detachment under all circumstances of life, from childhood&nbsp;to his death,&nbsp;that makes me wonder, was this\n a man or\n was this a\n God? Can a man even do something\n like this?\n It is as if there is a part of\n Krshna who is\n always separate\n from everything, and silently watches the whole scene with a bemused smile. He had not a single personal stake in the Mahabharata. Rama at least had his wife abducted for him to start a war against Ravana. But Krshna had zero&nbsp;personal stake in the Mahabharata.&nbsp;After liberating his parents from Kamsa, very soon he went off to meet the Pandavas. From out of nowhere he forced himself into the politics of the Mahabharata, and precipitated a great war to cleanse the world of burden. While Lakshmana devoutly followed Rama all along the Ramayana and they were like an inseparable pair, as&nbsp;Balarama in his next incarnation&nbsp;he could&nbsp;hardly understand Krshna. There are so many occassions where Balarama asks Krshna, what are they doing with all these kings, and&nbsp;that they should&nbsp;return to their village in Vrndavana. Krshna merely smiles. He knows that not everyone will understand everything. But that cannot stop him from following\n his dharma, with perfect detachement from eveyrthing of this plane. Neither false praises, nor wrong accusations by his close people can affect him one bit. And I am not even counting the miracles he perfromed as a Divine Child. So I worship Krshna, because I have not yet met or heard of read of&nbsp;a single sadhaka or saint or ordinary man or mahatma&nbsp;who has displayed this kind of perfected detachment through thick and thin, yet not withdrawing from the world or actively performing a larger dharma.&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_110 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_160 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_174&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_111 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_161 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_175&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;I started appreciating Swami Vivekanada more after I understood a bit of the Krshna Avatara. That was the last known saint who lived a whirlwind life in the middle of a circus-stoplight of fame and accusations, on one side adoring admirers and on the other bitter enemies accusing him of&nbsp;being a heretic&nbsp;right upto the&nbsp;very end of his brief life,&nbsp;and yet none of that affected him to any great degree. He faced terrific racism in the America, yet not a single speech of his reflects the slightest trace of bitterness, anger, or negativity. That is such a fantastic achievement, IMHO.&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_112 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_162 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_176&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_113 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_163 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_177&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;I agree with you, Narasimha, for most of us it is better to&nbsp;try to&nbsp;mould ones life&nbsp;with the same kind of supreme selflessness that Rama showed all along.&nbsp;Not just worship Rama&nbsp;but more importantly study&nbsp;his life and imbibe,&nbsp;to whatever degree possible, the quality he represented.&nbsp;Maybe, just maybe, then the Unmanifested Reality - Shiva - will fix the mind so firmly on that Reality, that in some future life, in some later birth, one will be able to live life like Krshna showed, unattached and unaffected by any dirt that the world throws up. And then the&nbsp;Universal&nbsp;Chit-Shakti (Adya Shakti)&nbsp;will flood such an\n individual with\n oppulence unimaginable, of\n this world and\n also of&nbsp;what lies in other\n worlds, like\n Krshna&#39;s six\n oppulences -&nbsp;Infinite wealth, infinite beauty, infinite power/knowledge, infinite fame, and infinite detachment from all the other five. &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_114 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_164 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_178&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_115 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_165 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_179&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_116 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_166 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_180&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;Enjoyed this discussion. :)&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_117 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_167 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_181&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_118 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_168 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_182&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:16px;&quot;&gt;Jai Jai&nbsp;Rama Krshna Hari!&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_32_1367853193997_119 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_37_1367796055441_169 yiv1276886991yui_3_7_2_27_1368126251839_183&quot; style=&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:Couri